#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.122"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.122:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.122:0.2"
msgid "12. Dhammakathikavagga"
msgstr "12. A Dhamma speaker"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 122. Sīlavantasutta → sīlasuttaṃ (bj) | sīlam (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.122:0.3"
msgid "122. Sīlavantasutta"
msgstr "122. An Ethical Mendicant"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.168"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: mahākoṭṭhiko → mahākoṭṭhito (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.122:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahākoṭṭhiko bārāṇasiyaṃ "
"viharanti isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Sāriputta and Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita were staying near "
"Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana."

msgctxt "sn22.122:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"sāriputto tenupasaṅkami … pe … etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita came out of retreat, went "
"to Venerable Sāriputta, and said:"

msgctxt "sn22.122:1.3"
msgid ""
"“sīlavatāvuso, sāriputta, bhikkhunā katame dhammā yoniso manasikātabbā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Sāriputta, what things should an ethical mendicant properly attend "
"to?”"

msgctxt "sn22.122:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Sīlavatāvuso, koṭṭhika, bhikkhunā pañcupādānakkhandhā aniccato dukkhato "
"rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato "
"yoniso manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Koṭṭhita, an ethical mendicant should properly attend to the five "
"grasping aggregates as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an "
"abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, "
"as empty, as not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.122:1.5"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn22.122:1.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"That is, the grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.122:1.7"
msgid ""
"Sīlavatāvuso, koṭṭhika, bhikkhunā ime pañcupādānakkhandhā aniccato dukkhato "
"rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato "
"yoniso manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"An ethical mendicant should properly attend to these five grasping "
"aggregates as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a "
"dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as "
"not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.122:1.8"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ sīlavā bhikkhu ime "
"pañcupādānakkhandhe aniccato … pe … anattato yoniso manasi karonto "
"sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikareyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that an ethical mendicant who regards the five grasping "
"aggregates in this way will realize the fruit of stream-entry.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.122:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Sotāpannena panāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā katame dhammā yoniso manasi "
"kātabbā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Reverend Sāriputta, what things should a mendicant stream-enterer "
"properly attend to?”"

msgctxt "sn22.122:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Sotāpannenapi kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, bhikkhunā ime pañcupādānakkhandhā "
"aniccato … pe … anattato yoniso manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"“A mendicant stream-enterer should properly attend to these five grasping "
"aggregates as impermanent … as not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.122:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ sotāpanno bhikkhu ime "
"pañcupādānakkhandhe aniccato … pe … anattato yoniso manasi karonto "
"sakadāgāmiphalaṃ sacchikareyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that a mendicant stream-enterer who regards the five grasping "
"aggregates in this way will realize the fruit of once-return.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.122:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Sakadāgāminā panāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā katame dhammā yoniso manasi "
"kātabbā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Reverend Sāriputta, what things should a mendicant once-returner "
"properly attend to?”"

msgctxt "sn22.122:3.2"
msgid ""
"“Sakadāgāmināpi kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, bhikkhunā ime pañcupādānakkhandhā "
"aniccato … pe … anattato yoniso manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"“A mendicant once-returner should properly attend to these five grasping "
"aggregates as impermanent … as not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.122:3.3"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ sakadāgāmī bhikkhu ime "
"pañcupādānakkhandhe aniccato … pe … anattato yoniso manasi karonto "
"anāgāmiphalaṃ sacchikareyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that a mendicant once-returner who regards the five grasping "
"aggregates in this way will realize the fruit of non-return.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.122:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Anāgāminā panāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā katame dhammā yoniso manasi "
"kātabbā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Reverend Sāriputta, what things should a mendicant non-returner "
"properly attend to?”"

msgctxt "sn22.122:4.2"
msgid ""
"“Anāgāmināpi kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, bhikkhunā ime pañcupādānakkhandhā aniccato "
"… pe … anattato yoniso manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"“A mendicant non-returner should properly attend to these five grasping "
"aggregates as impermanent … as not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.122:4.3"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ anāgāmī bhikkhu ime "
"pañcupādānakkhandhe aniccato … pe … anattato yoniso manasi karonto arahattaṃ "
"sacchikareyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that a mendicant non-returner who regards the five grasping "
"aggregates in this way will realize perfection.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.169"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.122:5.1"
msgid "“Arahatā panāvuso sāriputta, katame dhammā yoniso manasi kātabbā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Reverend Sāriputta, what things should a perfected one properly attend "
"to?”"

msgctxt "sn22.122:5.2"
msgid ""
"“Arahatāpi kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, ime pañcupādānakkhandhe aniccato dukkhato "
"rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato "
"yoniso manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Koṭṭhita, a perfected one should properly attend to the five "
"grasping aggregates as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an "
"abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, "
"as empty, as not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.122:5.3"
msgid "Natthi, khvāvuso, arahato uttari karaṇīyaṃ katassa vā paticayo;"
msgstr ""
"A perfected one has nothing more to do, and nothing that needs improvement."

msgctxt "sn22.122:5.4"
msgid ""
"api ca ime dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārāya ceva "
"saṃvattanti satisampajaññāya cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Still, these things, when developed and cultivated, lead to blissful "
"meditation in the present life, and also to mindfulness and situational "
"awareness.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.122:5.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
